main event: An observer reported seeing two star-like white objects moving in different directions while looking at the stars at Fort Carson, Colorado, on May 26, 1966.
interesting points: The observer saw the objects moving at different speeds and directions., The conclusion of the investigation stated that the sighting was caused by aircraft with navigation lights., The observer initially thought one of the objects was a star used as a reference point., The movement of the first object lasted approximately 30 seconds to 1 minute before it stopped., The report included sketches demonstrating the positions and movements of the objects.
witness description: Observer's identity is withheld; provided a detailed report of the sighting.
